{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:19:08.781Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cross-agent audit logs for compliance"},{"type":"text","text":" are immutable, structured records that capture "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"who did what, when, with what input, and with what result"},{"type":"text","text":" across every agent in a distributed swarm, so you can prove to auditors, regulators, or internal governance that autonomous AI work was performed safely, respectfully of data boundaries, and within policy. In a multi-agent swarm where an orchestrator spawns dozens of specialists (scraper, analyst, writer), cross-agent audit logs stitch their actions into a single, queryable trail that spans the entire run, not just individual agents."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cross-agent audit logs capture:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Identity"},{"type":"text","text":": Which agent (orchestrator, scraper, analyst) performed the action.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Timestamp"},{"type":"text","text":": When the action occurred (ISO 8601, with timezone).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Action type"},{"type":"text","text":": What happened (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"invoke_llm"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"call_tool"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"read_memory"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"write_output"},{"type":"text","text":").\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Inputs"},{"type":"text","text":": The prompt, user goal, tool arguments.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Outputs"},{"type":"text","text":": The response, tool result, final artifact.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Context"},{"type":"text","text":": User ID, run ID, tenant ID, region.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Outcome"},{"type":"text","text":": Success/failure, error message, tokens used, cost.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Integrity"},{"type":"text","text":": Cryptographic hash or signature to prove the record wasn’t tampered with."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the difference between "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ad-hoc logs"},{"type":"text","text":" (scattered across services) and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"compliance-ready audit logs"},{"type":"text","text":" (structured, immutable, queryable, and signed)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without cross-agent audit logs:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can’t prove compliance"},{"type":"text","text":": You can’t show auditors that agents didn’t access unauthorized data.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can’t debug failures"},{"type":"text","text":": You don’t know which agent failed or why.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can’t track cost"},{"type":"text","text":": You don’t know how many tokens each agent spent.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can’t enforce policies"},{"type":"text","text":": You can’t detect if an agent violated a rule (e.g., accessed PII)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"With cross-agent audit logs:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can prove compliance"},{"type":"text","text":": You can show auditors a complete trail of every action.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can debug fast"},{"type":"text","text":": You can query “show me all failures for run_id=abc123”.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can track cost"},{"type":"text","text":": You can sum tokens/cost per agent, per user, per tenant.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can enforce policies"},{"type":"text","text":": You can detect violations (e.g., agent accessed PII) and alert."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is critical for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"regulated industries"},{"type":"text","text":" (healthcare, finance, government) where you must prove that AI didn’t violate data privacy or security policies."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of audit logs as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"courtroom transcript"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Witness"},{"type":"text","text":": Which agent (orchestrator, scraper).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Time"},{"type":"text","text":": When the action happened.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Statement"},{"type":"text","text":": What the agent did (prompt, tool call).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":": What the agent output (response, artifact).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Signature"},{"type":"text","text":": Proof the transcript wasn’t altered."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every agent in the swarm “speaks” into the same transcript, so you can replay the entire run."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Structured logging"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every agent writes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"structured logs"},{"type":"text","text":" (JSON) instead of plain text:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-22T19:18:00Z\",\n  \"agent_id\": \"scraper_jp_ecommerce\",\n  \"run_id\": \"abc123\",\n  \"user_id\": \"user_123\",\n  \"action\": \"invoke_llm\",\n  \"inputs\": {\n    \"prompt\": \"Scrape pricing from example.com\",\n    \"model\": \"claude-3.5\",\n    \"tokens\": 1000\n  },\n  \"outputs\": {\n    \"response\": \"{\\\"price\\\": \\\"$19.99\\\"}\",\n    \"status\": \"success\"\n  },\n  \"cost\": 0.05\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is queryable (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"SELECT FROM logs WHERE run_id='abc123'"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Centralized log aggregation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Logs are sent to a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"centralized log store"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., Elasticsearch, OpenSearch, Datadog):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# agent_worker.py\nimport logging\nimport json\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"agent_worker\")\n\ndef log_action(agent_id: str, run_id: str, action: str, inputs: dict, outputs: dict):\n    log_entry = {\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"agent_id\": agent_id,\n        \"run_id\": run_id,\n        \"action\": action,\n        \"inputs\": inputs,\n        \"outputs\": outputs\n    }\n    logger.info(json.dumps(log_entry))"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A log aggregator (e.g., Fluentd, Logstash) collects logs and sends them to the store."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Immutable storage"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Logs are stored in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"immutable storage"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., S3 with Object Lock, WORM storage):\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No deletion"},{"type":"text","text":": Logs can’t be deleted once written.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No modification"},{"type":"text","text":": Logs can’t be altered once written.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Retention policy"},{"type":"text","text":": Logs are kept for a defined period (e.g., 7 years)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This proves to auditors that logs weren’t tampered with."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. Cryptographic signing"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each log entry is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"cryptographically signed"},{"type":"text","text":" to prove integrity:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import hashlib\nimport hmac\n\ndef sign_log_entry(log_entry: dict, secret_key: str):\n    log_json = json.dumps(log_entry)\n    signature = hmac.new(secret_key.encode(), log_json.encode(), hashlib.sha256).hexdigest()\n    return signature"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auditors can verify the signature to prove the log wasn’t altered."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. Query and visualization"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can query logs by:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run ID"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"SELECT FROM logs WHERE run_id='abc123'"},{"type":"text","text":" (shows entire run).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Agent ID"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"SELECT FROM logs WHERE agent_id='scraper_jp_ecommerce'"},{"type":"text","text":" (shows all scraper actions).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Action type"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"SELECT FROM logs WHERE action='invoke_llm'"},{"type":"text","text":" (shows all LLM calls).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"User ID"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"SELECT FROM logs WHERE user_id='user_123'"},{"type":"text","text":" (shows all actions for a user)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Dashboards show:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Per-run metrics"},{"type":"text","text":": Latency, tokens, cost, status.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aggregated metrics"},{"type":"text","text":": p95 latency, total cost, failure rate.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Anomaly detection"},{"type":"text","text":": Loops, token escalation, repeated prompts."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical cross-agent audit log stack:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Orchestrator (writes audit log)                          │\n│  ↓                                                        │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐   │\n│  │ Scraper      │  │ Analyst      │  │ Writer       │   │\n│  │ (writes log) │  │ (writes log) │  │ (writes log) │   │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘   │\n│       ↓                 ↓                    ↓           │\n│  Log Aggregator (Fluentd, Logstash)                      │\n│  ↓                                                        │\n│  Centralized Log Store (Elasticsearch, OpenSearch)       │\n│  ↓                                                        │\n│  Immutable Storage (S3 with Object Lock, WORM)           │\n│  ↓                                                        │\n│  Query & Visualization (Dashboards, Alerting)            │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every agent writes to the same log store, so you can query “show me all actions for run_id=abc123”."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prove compliance"},{"type":"text","text":": Show auditors a complete trail of every action."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Debug fast"},{"type":"text","text":": Query “show me all failures for run_id=abc123”."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Track cost"},{"type":"text","text":": Sum tokens/cost per agent, per user, per tenant."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Enforce policies"},{"type":"text","text":": Detect violations (e.g., agent accessed PII) and alert."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Aligns with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"compliance requirements"},{"type":"text","text":" (HIPAA, SOC 2, ISO 27001).\n- Works with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"any log store"},{"type":"text","text":" (Elasticsearch, OpenSearch, Datadog).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No code changes"},{"type":"text","text":" needed (just write structured JSON logs)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trade-offs:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adds storage cost"},{"type":"text","text":": Logs are stored (can be expensive at scale).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adds querying complexity"},{"type":"text","text":": You need to index logs for fast queries.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Requires retention policy"},{"type":"text","text":": You need to define how long to keep logs."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Write structured logs"},{"type":"text","text":": JSON, not plain text."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Include context"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"run_id"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"user_id"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"tenant_id"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"region"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sign logs"},{"type":"text","text":": Cryptographic signature to prove integrity."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Store immutably"},{"type":"text","text":": S3 with Object Lock, WORM storage."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define retention"},{"type":"text","text":": Keep logs for a defined period (e.g., 7 years)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Query by run ID"},{"type":"text","text":": Show entire run for debugging."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Monitor anomalies"},{"type":"text","text":": Loops, token escalation, policy violations."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cross-agent audit logs = "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"structured, immutable, signed records"},{"type":"text","text":" of every action across all agents in a swarm."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"They capture "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"identity, timestamp, action, inputs, outputs, context, outcome, integrity"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"They let you "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prove compliance"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"debug fast"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"track cost"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"enforce policies"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is critical for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"regulated industries"},{"type":"text","text":" where you must prove AI didn’t violate data privacy or security."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
